cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper deals with stochastic optimal control for robotic applications, specifically in the context of interaction with the environment. The paper discusses the inclusion of measurement uncertainty in the control algorithm, which is a key aspect of robotics and control systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also discusses the use of an observer to explicitly account for measurement uncertainty, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of risk-sensitive control is a common technique in machine learning and optimization, which could place the paper under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper includes simulation results on a 2D manipulator, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the manipulator is using visual feedback.
